{"type":"message","id":"34147192","parentId":"7fb44fbc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:49:12.699Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a completely different approach. Since the OpenClaw feishu integration seems to be sending file paths as URLs rather than uploading the actual files, maybe I should try to upload the file directly to Feishu's servers using their API, and then send the message with the file token.\n\nFeishu's file upload API for IM messages requires:\n1. Upload the file first to get a file_key\n2. Send a message with the file_key\n\nLet me try this approach using curl directly.\n\nActually, I need to check if there's a Feishu app access token I can use. Let me check the openclaw config for feishu settings.","thinkingSignature":"50f828617e4fd241153bdcea750ef63c348a5dcb70bd16718a0f0f0155d9e669"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9isptms33hhr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); feishu=d.get('channels',{}).get('feishu',{}); print('app_id:', feishu.get('appId','N/A')); print('has app_secret:', bool(feishu.get('appSecret')))\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"config parse failed\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":40626,"output":254,"cacheRead":18418,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59298,"cost":{"input":0.012187799999999999,"output":0.0003048,"cacheRead":0.0005525399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.013045139999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774352945094}}
