{"type":"message","id":"c1187b33","parentId":"414617e4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:50:51.709Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see that the Feishu app has `drive:drive` and `drive:file:upload` permissions. This means I can potentially upload the video to Feishu Drive and then share the file from there.\n\nBut more importantly, I notice that the OpenClaw Feishu plugin's `message` tool with `media` or `filePath` should be able to send files, but it seems like it's just embedding URLs rather than actually uploading.\n\nWait, I also notice `im:resource` which is for IM resource handling. Let me try a different approach - maybe I should upload the file to Feishu Drive first using the drive API, and then send the file message.\n\n\nThe `filePath` parameter might not be uploading the file to Feishu's servers at all - it could just be passing a local path that Feishu can't access. Since I have `drive:file:upload` permissions, I should upload to Drive first and then send the file from there. But the simplest solution might be to serve the file via a local HTTP server if the user can access the machine directly.\n\nWait, the user is on Feishu, so they're probably external to this network anyway. Let me try using the Feishu Drive upload API directly with the app's tenant token instead of trying to work around the OpenClaw plugin limitations.\n\nActually, I could use `feishu_doc` with the upload_file action if that's available, but looking at the message tool docs, it seems like passing the file path should work. Let me reconsider what the original error actually meant - the user said not to send a video address, they want the actual video file sent directly through the chat.\n\nMaybe the issue is that when I sent the message, it only delivered a URL preview instead of uploading the file itself. Since the OpenClaw Feishu plugin might be using file_key messaging rather than true file uploads, it could be sending a link instead of the actual file. Let me try using the message tool's `media` parameter instead and see if that triggers an actual upload to Feishu's servers.\n\nActually, the more straightforward solution is to leverage the Feishu Drive API since the app has the `drive:file:upload` scope. I can upload the video there first and then send the Drive link through the chat.","thinkingSignature":"b96ba1120946cddc99a689a8d5d1b58bd9f1230c4ebedfd7ef764042f7eb689f"},{"type":"text","text":"飞书有 Drive 上传权限。我先把视频上传到飞书云盘，再分享给你：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vonp4usysf2x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nd = json.load(sys.stdin)\n# Check for feishu in plugins or extensions\nprint('channels:', list(d.get('channels', {}).keys()))\nprint('plugins:', list(d.get('plugins', {}).keys()) if 'plugins' in d else 'N/A')\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48071,"output":605,"cacheRead":18418,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67094,"cost":{"input":0.0144213,"output":0.000726,"cacheRead":0.0005525399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01569984}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774353025584}}
