{"type":"message","id":"8b63b0b9","parentId":"1b3e4684","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:52:33.099Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can access Feishu Drive. Now let me try to upload the video file to Feishu Drive. I need to use the drive API to upload a file. Let me check if there's a feishu_drive tool that supports file upload.Actually, looking at the feishu_drive tool description:```\nActions: list, info, create_folder, move, delete\n```There's no file upload action in the feishu_drive tool. The `drive:file:upload` scope exists but the tool doesn't expose it.Let me try another approach. Let me look at how the sendMediaFeishu function works and see if there's a way to add the workspace directory to the allowed list. \n\nI need to check the gateway configuration or the feishu plugin settings to see where mediaLocalRoots is defined.","thinkingSignature":"7cacd34dddfde3ecde3b15388a3094cacee17f914c35f03fbef581aa1cf9facb"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3k358vx9ngic_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -rn \"mediaLocalRoots\\|localRoot\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/extensions/feishu/src/ 2>/dev/null | grep -v \".test.\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54347,"output":238,"cacheRead":18418,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73003,"cost":{"input":0.0163041,"output":0.0002856,"cacheRead":0.0005525399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01714224}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774353145460}}
