{"type":"message","id":"fb9de0a5","parentId":"8a452f05","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:52:41.600Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `mediaLocalRoots` is passed from the core outbound context. This is a system-level configuration that determines which directories are allowed for media access. The error says the file path `/home/hochoy/.openclaw/workspace-comedy/projects/video-pipeline/out/video-weiqing.mp4` is not under an allowed directory.\n\nThe `mediaLocalRoots` is likely set from the OpenClaw core config. Let me check if there's a core config option for mediaLocalRoots.\n\nLet me look at the OpenClaw docs to see if there's a way to configure allowed media directories.Actually, the quickest solution might be to configure the `feishu.capabilities.mediaLocalRoots` in the openclaw config, or simply to use the `openclaw config` command to see what settings are available.\n \nLet me try running the OpenClaw config command to see what media-related settings are actually available.","thinkingSignature":"767296bd016183b68c623d083c7ca9522beafff824eb23cf174fd9a53db87f6c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7adjix3pt8js_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw config list 2>&1 | head -30","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54944,"output":232,"cacheRead":18418,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73594,"cost":{"input":0.0164832,"output":0.0002784,"cacheRead":0.0005525399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.017314140000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774353153138}}
