{"type":"message","id":"160d451e","parentId":"92cacfc2","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:41:09.384Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me try a different approach. Instead of trying to re-encode, let me try to change Remotion's output settings or just re-render with different settings. Actually, let me try a simpler approach - use ffmpeg to just copy the video stream but lower the audio bitrate and see if that alone helps. Actually that won't reduce video size.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The issue is the file is 47MB. What if I use ffmpeg to:\n1. Take the video stream but lower the resolution\n2. Keep the H264 stream as-is (since copy works)\n\nNo wait, if I use stream copy, the size won't change.\n\nWhat about using ffmpeg with the `-g` option to add temporal pooling or something? No.\n\nActually, let me check if the 8.6MB video-weiqing.mp4 (the pure subtitle version) was successfully sent earlier. The user said they didn't receive it, but maybe it was sent and they missed it. Let me try sending the 7.2MB video-v2.mp4 instead since it already uploaded successfully to Feishu before.","thinkingSignature":"d81512da705cbff5d7b7e574bbe76b03ea4d15f0f7808d766cbbfaf9a638dd20"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zsyub04w4rd0_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","sessionId":"amber-falcon","timeout":15000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":81134,"output":283,"cacheRead":18418,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":99835,"cost":{"input":0.0243402,"output":0.00033959999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0005525399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02523234}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774356057931}}
