{"type":"message","id":"9a41b634","parentId":"8f6be31a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:41:51.569Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pure subtitle version (3.9MB) was sent. Now let me try to compress the 47MB version using a different approach. Since all hardware encoders fail, let me try using python with ffmpeg-python or imageio, or try a totally different approach.\n\nActually, let me try a simple approach - use ffmpeg with the `-Intra` flag (intra-only, no interframe compression) and see if that reduces size. No that would make it larger.\n\nActually, I know - let me try using ffmpeg's raw H.264 output and then mux it. Or better yet, let me try using the `-limit_rate` option or `-fs` (file size limit) with ffmpeg.\n \nI could pipe the video through ffmpeg with H.264 encoding and a tight bitrate constraint to force the file size down. But I should verify the bitrate on that smaller video-weiqing.mp4 file first to understand what compression is actually needed.","thinkingSignature":"b4f93808afd69b4d630cec2b43d0b3e295a648419c0c0676a0c97702a0157e30"},{"type":"text","text":"3.9MB 纯字幕版已发送。现在尝试压缩 47MB 的配图版：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6d6gtlx4n9ej_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ffprobe -v quiet -show_streams /home/hochoy/.openclaw/workspace-comedy/projects/video-pipeline/out/video-weiqing.mp4 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"codec_name|width|height|bit_rate\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":82501,"output":301,"cacheRead":18418,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":101220,"cost":{"input":0.0247503,"output":0.0003612,"cacheRead":0.0005525399999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.02566404}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774356099333}}
