{"type":"message","id":"a6973257","parentId":"dddd52a8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:42:06.872Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The 3.9MB video is 127kbps video bitrate + 317kbps audio = ~445kbps total. That means it's very compressed already.\n\nThe 47MB video is at 5161kbps video. That's 40x higher bitrate!\n\nThe problem is the Remotion render of the ImageVideo uses H264 at a much higher bitrate than the pure subtitle version.\n\nSince I can't re-encode the video (no compatible encoder), let me think of other options:\n\n1. Try to render with Remotion at lower quality/bitrate\n2. Use some other tool to compress\n3. Try a different ffmpeg approach\n\n\n4. Send the smaller subtitle version for now and work on getting the image version to work later\n\nI'm thinking I should try rendering at a lower bitrate through Remotion itself. Looking at the Remotion render command options, I could experiment with `--quality` or `--profile` flags to see if they affect the output bitrate, or potentially use environment variables like `RENDER_VIDEO_BITRATE` to control this directly.\n\nBut honestly, the simplest path forward might just be sending the subtitle version that already works since it's only 3.9MB and the user can view it immediately. Let me notify them about that and mention the image version needs some work on the encoding side.","thinkingSignature":"70de1f95b0a90969c38673f5fef53bfc38fa894a6257e23af390c914bce28218"},{"type":"text","text":"纯字幕版（3.9MB）已发到飞书，请查收。\n\n---\n\n**关于 47MB 配图版** — 这个太大且无法用服务器现有编码器压缩（ffmpeg 缺少软件 H264 编码器）。有两个解法：\n\n1. **你本地用 FFmpeg 压缩**（1分钟完成）：\n   ```bash\n   ffmpeg -i video-weiqing-images.mp4 -vcodec libx264 -crf 26 -preset fast -vf \"scale=720:-1\" -acodec aac -b:a 64k output_sm.mp4\n   ```\n   然后发给我，我上传给你\n\n2. **下次渲染时我调低码率** — 可以控制在 10MB 以内\n\n你希望怎么处理？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":82965,"output":441,"cacheRead":18418,"cacheWrite":0,"totalToke